        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 2:42PM PDT by NWS San Diego CA</headline>
        <description>At 242 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
southwestern Lucerne Valley. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lucerne Valley, Hwy 18 Between Baldwin Lake And Lucerne Valley,
Baldwin Lake, and western Johnson Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
